{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":13,"text":"Over the past six months, I've spent my time"},{"time":3856,"text":"traveling. I think I've done 60,000 miles,"},{"time":7247,"text":"but without leaving my desk."},{"time":10169,"text":"And the reason I can do that is because I'm actually two people."},{"time":13015,"text":"I look like one person but I'm two people. I'm Eddie who is here,"},{"time":15968,"text":"and at the same time, my alter ego is a big green boxy"},{"time":20369,"text":"avatar nicknamed Cyber Frank."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24049,"text":"So that's what I spend my time doing. I'd like to start,"},{"time":26858,"text":"if it's possible, with a test, because I do business stuff,"},{"time":29920,"text":"so it's important that we focus on outcomes."},{"time":33504,"text":"And then I struggled, because I was thinking to myself,"},{"time":35437,"text":"\"What should I talk? What should I do? It's a TED audience."},{"time":37905,"text":"It's got to be stretching. How am I going to make — ?\""},{"time":40713,"text":"So I just hope I've got the level of difficulty right."},{"time":43806,"text":"So let's just walk our way through this."},{"time":45870,"text":"Please could you work this through with me? You can shout out the answer if you like."},{"time":49319,"text":"The question is, which of these horizontal lines is longer?"},{"time":51501,"text":"The answer is?"},{"time":52647,"text":"Audience: The same.Eddie Obeng: The same."},{"time":55371,"text":"No, they're not the same. (Laughter)"},{"time":57118,"text":"They're not the same. The top one is 10 percent longer than the bottom one."},{"time":60747,"text":"So why did you tell me they were the same? Do you remember when we were kids at school,"},{"time":64056,"text":"about that big, they played the same trick on us?"},{"time":66511,"text":"It was to teach us parallax. Do you remember?"},{"time":68848,"text":"And you got, you said, \"It's the same!\" And you got it wrong."},{"time":71995,"text":"You remember? And you learned the answer, and you've carried this answer in your head for 10, 20, 30, 40 years:"},{"time":75831,"text":"The answer is the same. The answer is the same. So when you're asked what the lengths are,"},{"time":79711,"text":"you say they're the same, but they're not the same, because I've changed it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82280,"text":"And this is what I'm trying to explain has happened to us in the 21st century."},{"time":86447,"text":"Somebody or something has changed the rules"},{"time":88745,"text":"about how our world works."},{"time":90802,"text":"When I'm joking, I try and explain it happened at midnight,"},{"time":93708,"text":"you see, while we were asleep, but it was midnight 15 years ago. Okay?"},{"time":97544,"text":"You didn't notice it? But basically, what they do is,"},{"time":100159,"text":"they switched all the rules round, so that the way to"},{"time":102831,"text":"successfully run a business, an organization, or even a country,"},{"time":106423,"text":"has been deleted, flipped, and it's a completely new"},{"time":109104,"text":"— you think I'm joking, don't you — there's a completely new set of rules in operation. (Laughter)"},{"time":113384,"text":"Did you notice that? I mean, you missed this one."},{"time":115194,"text":"You probably — No, you didn't. Okay. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":117029,"text":"My simple idea is that what's happened is,"},{"time":121371,"text":"the real 21st century around us isn't so obvious to us,"},{"time":125365,"text":"so instead we spend our time responding rationally"},{"time":128410,"text":"to a world which we understand and recognize,"},{"time":131583,"text":"but which no longer exists."},{"time":134002,"text":"You don't believe me, do you? Okay. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":136211,"text":"So let me take you on a little journey of many of the things I don't understand."},{"time":141115,"text":"If you search Amazon for the word \"creativity,\""},{"time":143707,"text":"you'll discover something like 90,000 books."},{"time":146074,"text":"If you go on Google and you look for \"innovation + creativity,\""},{"time":148878,"text":"you get 30 million hits. If you add the word \"consultants,\" it doubles to 60 million. (Laughter)"},{"time":153137,"text":"Are you with me? And yet, statistically, what you discover"},{"time":156322,"text":"is that about one in 100,000 ideas is found making money"},{"time":159307,"text":"or delivering benefits two years after its inception."},{"time":162430,"text":"It makes no sense. Companies make their expensive executives"},{"time":165443,"text":"spend ages carefully preparing forecasts and budgets"},{"time":168003,"text":"which are obsolete or need changing before they can be published."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172063,"text":"How is that possible? If you look at the visions we have,"},{"time":175786,"text":"the visions of how we're going to change the world,"},{"time":177563,"text":"the key thing is implementation. We have the vision."},{"time":180188,"text":"We've got to make it happen."},{"time":181544,"text":"We've spent decades professionalizing implementation."},{"time":184536,"text":"People are supposed to be good at making stuff happen."},{"time":186993,"text":"However, if I use as an example a family of five"},{"time":191890,"text":"going on holiday, if you can imagine this,"},{"time":194624,"text":"all the way from London all the way across to Hong Kong,"},{"time":199024,"text":"what I want you to think about is their budget is only 3,000 pounds of expenses."},{"time":202933,"text":"What actually happens is, if I compare this to the average"},{"time":206064,"text":"real project, average real successful project,"},{"time":211851,"text":"the family actually end up in Makassar, South Sulawesi,"},{"time":216077,"text":"at a cost of 4,000 pounds,"},{"time":219094,"text":"whilst leaving two of the children behind. (Laughter)"},{"time":221799,"text":"What I'm trying to explain to you is, there are things which don't make sense to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226134,"text":"It gets even worse than that. Let me just walk you through this one."},{"time":230419,"text":"This is a quote, and I'll just pick words out of it."},{"time":232993,"text":"It says -- I'll put on the voice -- \"In summary, your Majesty,"},{"time":236336,"text":"the failure to foresee the timing, extent and severity"},{"time":239842,"text":"of the crisis was due to the lack of creativity"},{"time":243605,"text":"and the number of bright minds,\" or something like that."},{"time":247003,"text":"This was a group of eminent economists apologizing to the Queen of England"},{"time":250811,"text":"when she asked the question,"},{"time":252816,"text":"\"Why did no one tell us that the crisis was coming?\" (Laughter)"},{"time":255755,"text":"I'll never get my knighthood. I'll never get my knighthood. (Laughter)"},{"time":259258,"text":"That's not the important point. The thing you have to remember is,"},{"time":261486,"text":"these are eminent economists, some of the smartest people"},{"time":264948,"text":"on the planet. Do you see the challenge? (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":268464,"text":"It's scary. My friend and mentor, Tim Brown of IDEO,"},{"time":273011,"text":"he explains that design must get big, and he's right."},{"time":276913,"text":"He wisely explains this to us. He says design thinking"},{"time":279532,"text":"must tackle big systems for the challenges we have."},{"time":281834,"text":"He's absolutely right."},{"time":283971,"text":"And then I ask myself, \"Why was it ever small?\""},{"time":287644,"text":"Isn't it weird? You know, if collaboration is so cool,"},{"time":291506,"text":"is cross-functional working is so amazing,"},{"time":293639,"text":"why did we build these huge hierarchies? What's going on?"},{"time":298865,"text":"You see, I think what's happened, perhaps, is that"},{"time":303146,"text":"we've not noticed that change I described earlier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307232,"text":"What we do know is that the world has accelerated."},{"time":310010,"text":"Cyberspace moves everything at the speed of light."},{"time":312332,"text":"Technology accelerates things exponentially."},{"time":314804,"text":"So if this is now, and that's the past,"},{"time":316966,"text":"and we start thinking about change, you know,"},{"time":318336,"text":"all governments are seeking change, you're here seeking change,"},{"time":320907,"text":"everybody's after change, it's really cool. (Laughter)"},{"time":323578,"text":"So what happens is, we get this wonderful whooshing acceleration and change."},{"time":328021,"text":"The speed is accelerating. That's not the only thing."},{"time":332117,"text":"At the same time, as we've done that, we've done something really weird."},{"time":334788,"text":"We've doubled the population in 40 years,"},{"time":337437,"text":"put half of them in cities, then connected them all up so they can interact."},{"time":341051,"text":"The density of the interaction of human beings is amazing."},{"time":343920,"text":"There are charts which show all these movements of information. That density of information is amazing."},{"time":348772,"text":"And then we've done a third thing."},{"time":350406,"text":"you know, for those of you who have as an office"},{"time":352401,"text":"a little desk underneath the stairs, and you say, well this is my little desk under the stairs,"},{"time":357870,"text":"no! You are sitting at the headquarters of a global corporation if you're connected to the Internet."},{"time":364261,"text":"What's happened is, we've changed the scale."},{"time":367175,"text":"Size and scale are no longer the same."},{"time":370122,"text":"And then add to that, every time you tweet,"},{"time":373344,"text":"over a third of your followers follow from a country"},{"time":376134,"text":"which is not your own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379042,"text":"Global is the new scale. We know that."},{"time":382051,"text":"And so people say things like, \"The world is now a turbulent place.\" Have you heard them saying things like that?"},{"time":386063,"text":"And they use it as a metaphor. Have you come across this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":388824,"text":"And they think it's a metaphor, but this is not a metaphor."},{"time":391957,"text":"It's reality. As a young engineering student, I remember"},{"time":395174,"text":"going to a demonstration where they basically,"},{"time":399165,"text":"the demonstrator did something quite intriguing."},{"time":401576,"text":"What he did was, he got a transparent pipe — have you seen this demonstration before? —"},{"time":406758,"text":"he attached it to a tap. So effectively what you had was,"},{"time":410174,"text":"you had a situation where — I'll try and draw the tap"},{"time":413349,"text":"and the pipe, actually I'll skip the tap. The taps are hard."},{"time":416064,"text":"Okay? So I'll write the word \"tap.\" Is that okay? It's a tap. (Laughter)"},{"time":419262,"text":"Okay, so he attaches it to a transparent pipe, and he turns the water on."},{"time":423064,"text":"And he says, do you notice anything? And the water is whooshing down this pipe."},{"time":425685,"text":"I mean, this is not exciting stuff. Are you with me?"},{"time":428806,"text":"So the water goes up. He turns it back down. Great."},{"time":432924,"text":"And he says, \"Anything you notice?\" No. Then he sticks a needle into the pipe,"},{"time":436636,"text":"and he connects this to a container, and he fills"},{"time":438812,"text":"the container up with green ink. You with me?"},{"time":442133,"text":"So guess what happens? A thin green line comes out"},{"time":445923,"text":"as it flows down the pipe. It's not that interesting."},{"time":450269,"text":"And then he turns the water up a bit, so it starts coming back in. And nothing changes."},{"time":454561,"text":"So he's changing the flow of the water, but it's just a boring green line."},{"time":457747,"text":"He adds some more. He adds some more. And then something weird happens."},{"time":460614,"text":"There's this little flicker, and then as he turns it ever so slightly more,"},{"time":465770,"text":"the whole of that green line disappears, and instead"},{"time":468745,"text":"there are these little sort of inky dust devils close to the needle."},{"time":472105,"text":"They're called eddies. Not me. And they're violently dispersing the ink"},{"time":475269,"text":"so that it actually gets diluted out, and the color's gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478953,"text":"What's happened in this world of pipe"},{"time":482966,"text":"is somebody has flipped it. They've changed the rules from laminar to turbulent."},{"time":486893,"text":"All the rules are gone. In that environment, instantly,"},{"time":490574,"text":"all the possibilities which turbulence brings are available,"},{"time":494693,"text":"and it's not the same as laminar."},{"time":497535,"text":"And if we didn't have that green ink, you'd never notice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502493,"text":"And I think this is our challenge, because somebody"},{"time":505790,"text":"has actually increased — and it's probably you guys with all your tech and stuff —"},{"time":509894,"text":"the speed, the scale and the density of interaction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513875,"text":"Now how do we cope and deal with that?"},{"time":515574,"text":"Well, we could just call it turbulence, or we could try and learn."},{"time":519007,"text":"Yes, learn, but I know you guys grew up in the days when"},{"time":524105,"text":"there were actually these things called correct answers,"},{"time":526909,"text":"because of the answer you gave me to the horizontal line puzzle,"},{"time":530070,"text":"and you believe it will last forever."},{"time":531883,"text":"So I'll put a little line up here which represents learning,"},{"time":535310,"text":"and that's how we used to do it. We could see things,"},{"time":537485,"text":"understand them, take the time to put them into practice."},{"time":539998,"text":"Out here is the world. Now, what's happened to our pace"},{"time":543847,"text":"of learning as the world has accelerated? Well, if you work"},{"time":547092,"text":"for a corporation, you'll discover it's quite difficult to work"},{"time":549638,"text":"on stuff which your boss doesn't approve of, isn't in the strategy,"},{"time":552584,"text":"and anyway, you've got to go through your monthly meetings."},{"time":555189,"text":"If you work in an institution, one day you will get them to make that decision."},{"time":560557,"text":"And if you work in a market where people believe in cycles,"},{"time":563292,"text":"it's even funnier, because you have to wait all the way"},{"time":565679,"text":"for the cycle to fail before you go, \"There's something wrong.\" You with me?"},{"time":569302,"text":"So it's likely that the line, in terms of learning, is pretty flat."},{"time":574854,"text":"You with me? This point over here, the point at which"},{"time":579051,"text":"the lines cross over, the pace of change"},{"time":582954,"text":"overtakes the pace of learning,"},{"time":586098,"text":"and for me, that is what I was describing"},{"time":588983,"text":"when I was telling you about midnight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592240,"text":"So what does it do to us? Well, it completely transforms what we have to do,"},{"time":595401,"text":"many mistakes we make. We solve last year's problems"},{"time":599040,"text":"without thinking about the future. If you try and think about it,"},{"time":601776,"text":"the things you're solving now, what problems are they going to bring in the future?"},{"time":604712,"text":"If you haven't understood the world you're living in,"},{"time":607232,"text":"it's almost impossible to be absolutely certain that what you're going to deliver fits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610848,"text":"I'll give you an example, a quick one. Creativity and ideas,"},{"time":614256,"text":"I mentioned that earlier. All the CEOs around me, my clients, they want innovation,"},{"time":617297,"text":"so they seek innovation. They say to people, \"Take risks and be creative!\""},{"time":620601,"text":"But unfortunately the words get transformed as they travel through the air."},{"time":623528,"text":"Entering their ears, what they hear is, \"Do crazy things and then I'll fire you.\" Why? (Laughter) Because —"},{"time":627649,"text":"Why? Because in the old world, okay, in the old world,"},{"time":631304,"text":"over here, getting stuff wrong was unacceptable."},{"time":633769,"text":"If you got something wrong, you'd failed. How should you be treated?"},{"time":636401,"text":"Well, harshly, because you could have asked somebody who had experience."},{"time":639537,"text":"So we learned the answer and we carried this in our heads for 20, 30 years, are you with me?"},{"time":644601,"text":"The answer is, don't do things which are different."},{"time":647304,"text":"And then suddenly we tell them to and it doesn't work."},{"time":649527,"text":"You see, in reality, there are two ways you can fail in our new world."},{"time":652139,"text":"One, you're doing something that you should follow a procedure to, and it's a very difficult thing,"},{"time":655990,"text":"you're sloppy, you get it wrong. How should you be treated? You should probably be fired."},{"time":659472,"text":"On the other hand, you're doing something new, no one's ever done before,"},{"time":662704,"text":"you get it completely wrong. How should you be treated?"},{"time":664684,"text":"Well, free pizzas! You should be treated better than the people who succeed."},{"time":668296,"text":"It's called smart failure. Why? Because you can't put it on your C.V."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671784,"text":"So what I want to leave you, then, is with the explanation"},{"time":674513,"text":"of why I actually traveled 60,000 miles from my desk."},{"time":678337,"text":"When I realized the power of this new world,"},{"time":680377,"text":"I quit my safe teaching job, and set up a virtual business school,"},{"time":684749,"text":"the first in the world, in order to teach people how to make this happen,"},{"time":688544,"text":"and I used some of my learnings about some of the rules which I'd learned on myself."},{"time":693877,"text":"If you're interested, worldaftermidnight.com, you'll find out more,"},{"time":696926,"text":"but I've applied them to myself for over a decade,"},{"time":699846,"text":"and I'm still here, and I still have my house, and the most important thing is,"},{"time":703595,"text":"I hope I've done enough to inject a little green ink into your lives,"},{"time":708975,"text":"so that when you go away and you're making your next"},{"time":711718,"text":"absolutely sensible and rational decision, you'll take some time to think,"},{"time":716317,"text":"\"Hmm, I wonder whether this also makes sense"},{"time":719397,"text":"in our new world after midnight.\" Thank you very much."},{"time":722180,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":729230,"text":"Thank you, thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}